# pnpm config for the Complaints CRS monorepo.
#
# We keep pnpm's default isolated linker so `apps/web` (React 19) and
# `apps/mobile` (React 18.3, pinned by RN 0.76) stay in their own
# `node_modules` trees and never collide. `node-linker=hoisted` was
# tried first but flattens the whole monorepo to one React version —
# the wrong fix.
#
# The only friction with the default isolated layout is that Metro
# (React Native's bundler) cannot resolve transitive peer deps from
# pnpm's `.pnpm/` symlink store. `public-hoist-pattern` lifts the
# RN ecosystem to the root visible `node_modules`, where Metro's
# hierarchical resolver finds them on a normal upward walk.
#
# React itself is deliberately NOT in the pattern list — hoisting it
# would force a single version across the monorepo and break either
# web (drops to 18.3) or mobile (RN 0.76 cannot support React 19).
public-hoist-pattern[]=@babel/runtime
public-hoist-pattern[]=@babel/runtime/*
public-hoist-pattern[]=@react-native/*
public-hoist-pattern[]=react-native
public-hoist-pattern[]=react-native-*
public-hoist-pattern[]=expo-modules-*
public-hoist-pattern[]=@expo/*
public-hoist-pattern[]=metro
public-hoist-pattern[]=metro-*

